archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel.documentation: Security Operations Center means different things to different organisations. What I have created here is a model that can be taken and adapted to suit your organisation. I started with the main Drivers, Principles and Goals of a Security operations capability and then develped the model around these. The diagram is broken down into several sections; 1. The business drivers - Why are we doing this? 2. The Roles and associated responsibilities within the SoC. This includes the roles and responsibilities outside of the SoC who contribute to the SoCs operation and sucess. 3. The core Security Capability Groups within the SoC which address each of the business drivers or specifically the goals. A Capability Group may support one or more services and a service might contain one or more mechanisms. For example Vulnerabilitiy Management is comprised of multiple services eg. Scanning, Patching, Testing, Secure Builds, and Breach Simulation. 4. Security Processes associated with the Capabilities. These are particularly important and require
